FBIS4-17050 "drsov077_u_94004" FBIS-SOV-94-077 Daily Report 20 Apr 1994 Latvia Cabinet Raises Minimum Salary, Sets Pensioner Rules Cabinet Raises Minimum Salary, Sets Pensioner Rules WS2004135294 Tallinn BNS in English 0922 GMT 20 Apr 94 WS2004135294 Tallinn BNS English BFN [Excerpt] Riga, Apr 20, BNS -- The Latvian Cabinet decided Tuesday [19 April] to raise the minimum salary from 15 lats (26 U.S. dollars) to 22.50 lats (38 U.S. dollars), the Cabinet's press secretary, Sergejs Ancupovs, said at a briefing. The government also determined regulations on order of giving pensions to those pensioners who still work. The regulations provide for the state employment services to find working places being vacant for two months. Pensioners will be allowed to take these jobs and receive both: pension and salary. [passage omitted]
